beyond your comprehension?

121
00:07:45.006 --> 00:07:47.508  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Despite possessing
physical powers

122
00:07:47.592 --> 00:07:49.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
far superior
to that of common man,

123
00:07:50.011 --> 00:07:52.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you cannot escape
the yoke of emotion,

124
00:07:52.221 --> 00:07:53.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
your weak point as cyborgs.

125
00:07:54.140 --> 00:07:55.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

126
00:07:55.224 --> 00:07:57.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's enough out of you.

127
00:07:57.185 --> 00:07:59.479  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We understand why you
spilled your guts to us,

128
00:07:59.562 --> 00:08:02.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but you still haven't shown us
anything to prove your story.

129
00:08:03.149 --> 00:08:05.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You can choose
not to acknowledge this.

130
00:08:05.568 --> 00:08:07.195  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do whatever you want.

131
00:08:07.278 --> 00:08:09.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's all I have
to say to you on this.

132
00:08:11.073 --> 00:08:13.367  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Françoise,
would you take a moment

133
00:08:13.451 --> 00:08:15.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to confirm
those rocket launches?

134
00:08:15.870 --> 00:08:18.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just a second.

135
00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:21.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes. All of the launch plans
she mentioned

136
00:08:21.417 --> 00:08:22.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
were announced earlier.

137
00:08:22.752 --> 00:08:25.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All of the rocket launches
were recorded

138
00:08:25.129 --> 00:08:27.089  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and completely
documented by NORAD.

139
00:08:27.256 --> 00:08:29.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There was likely
a launch today as well.

140
00:08:29.717 --> 00:08:31.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's correct.

141
00:08:31.511 --> 00:08:34.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It was 8:00 a.m. this morning,
Eastern Standard Time.

142
00:08:34.722 --> 00:08:37.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Catalina] That would have been
the last of the rockets.

143
00:08:37.350 --> 00:08:39.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Gilmore]
What do you mean "last"?

144
00:08:39.227 --> 00:08:40.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just what I said.

145
00:08:40.811 --> 00:08:43.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The work of this
particular rocket is delivering

146
00:08:43.356 --> 00:08:46.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
specialized attitude control
propellant to the station.

147
00:08:46.734 --> 00:08:51.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Once the station is replenished,
it will change course

148
00:08:51.197 --> 00:08:54.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and begin dropping
atmospheric reentry capsules

149
00:08:54.325 --> 00:08:56.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
loaded with micro-drones
toward the Earth below.

150
00:08:56.911 --> 00:08:59.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
After being dropped,
multiple reentry vehicles

151
00:08:59.247 --> 00:09:00.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
will separate from the capsules

152
00:09:01.040 --> 00:09:02.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
while passing
through the atmosphere,

153
00:09:02.667 --> 00:09:04.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and upon reaching
the stratosphere,

154
00:09:04.961 --> 00:09:06.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the reentry vehicles

155
00:09:06.337 --> 00:09:09.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
will subsequently
release the micro-drones.

156
00:09:09.257 --> 00:09:11.092  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[gasps]
-Hmm.

157
00:09:11.259 --> 00:09:14.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[sighs]
-[both gasp]

158
00:09:14.762 --> 00:09:17.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The virus being carried
by the micro-drones

159
00:09:17.890 --> 00:09:19.976  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
will be released
on the humans below.

160
00:09:20.059 --> 00:09:24.021  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It will proliferate even as it
forces its host to evolve.

161
00:09:24.105 --> 00:09:27.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As it's expelled into the air
through coughing and sneezing,

162
00:09:27.358 --> 00:09:29.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it will trigger
continuing infection.

163
00:09:29.777 --> 00:09:31.195  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hold on.
You're saying this contagion

164
00:09:31.404 --> 00:09:34.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-is spreading through the air?
-That's right.

165
00:09:34.782 --> 00:09:37.493  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Once that point is reached,
there will be no way

166
00:09:37.577 --> 00:09:40.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of preventing
the continuing contagion.

167
00:09:40.329 --> 00:09:43.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The contamination will spread
in an explosive fashion

168
00:09:43.374 --> 00:09:45.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
from person to person.

169
00:09:45.793 --> 00:09:47.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wait. What the bloody hell?

170
00:09:49.130 --> 00:09:50.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doctor.

171
00:09:50.298 --> 00:09:51.716  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm.

172
00:09:51.799 --> 00:09:54.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Unfortunately we have no choice
but to believe her.

173
00:09:54.802 --> 00:09:55.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

174
00:09:56.095 --> 00:09:57.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Françoise, what's the status

175
00:09:57.763 --> 00:09:59.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of the rocket
that launched this morning?

176
00:10:01.767 --> 00:10:04.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The unmanned supply vehicle
has already separated

177
00:10:04.687 --> 00:10:06.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and is on trajectory
for the station's orbit.

178
00:10:07.106 --> 00:10:10.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's due to arrive
in approximately eight hours.

179
00:10:10.359 --> 00:10:12.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We really
only have eight hours?

180
00:10:12.194 --> 00:10:13.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps] Doctor...

181
00:10:13.738 --> 00:10:15.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
are there any weapons
on this ship

182
00:10:15.531 --> 00:10:17.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
we can use to shoot it down?

183
00:10:17.366 --> 00:10:18.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ideally I'd say no.

184
00:10:19.160 --> 00:10:21.245  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Catalina] I don't recommend it.

185
00:10:21.329 --> 00:10:23.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Once the station is destroyed,

186
00:10:23.456 --> 00:10:25.833  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the micro-drones
will scatter through its orbit

187
00:10:25.916 --> 00:10:27.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
along with the other debris.

188
00:10:28.377 --> 00:10:30.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then of course,
they will eventually be drawn in

189
00:10:31.005 --> 00:10:32.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
by the Earth's
gravitational pull

190
00:10:32.840 --> 00:10:34.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and rain down on the ground.

191
00:10:34.842 --> 00:10:36.010  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gilmore] Surely many drones

192
00:10:36.093 --> 00:10:37.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
would never even breach
the atmosphere.

193
00:10:38.054 --> 00:10:39.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That may be true,

194
00:10:39.597 --> 00:10:42.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but they threaten mankind
should any reach the ground.

195
00:10:42.808 --> 00:10:45.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Also, for the same reason,
it would be risky

196
00:10:45.978 --> 00:10:48.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to use ground-based fire
on the reentry capsules.

197
00:10:48.481 --> 00:10:49.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then just what do you suggest?

198
00:10:50.107 --> 00:10:52.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your best chance
is to go to the station.

199
00:10:52.902 --> 00:10:55.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Once there, you could deflect
all of the virus

200
00:10:55.237 --> 00:10:57.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
from Earth's orbit
into the void of outer space.

201
00:10:59.825 --> 00:11:02.161  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You say that
like there's nothing to it.

202
00:11:02.328 --> 00:11:05.665  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But the Dolphin III is not able
to go beyond the atmosphere.

203
00:11:05.831 --> 00:11:09.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[groans] So you're saying
there's nothing more we can do?

204
00:11:10.127 --> 00:11:13.172  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No. We're not
out of options yet.

205
00:11:13.339 --> 00:11:15.132  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[cyborgs gasp]

206
00:11:19.845 --> 00:11:21.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[G.B.] A rocket, huh?

207
00:11:21.847 --> 00:11:24.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You mean fly
to outer space in that?

208
00:11:24.350 --> 00:11:26.435  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Usually this device
would be used

209
00:11:26.519 --> 00:11:29.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to intercept other missiles
at high altitude.

210
00:11:29.271 --> 00:11:31.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can uncouple the warhead,

211
00:11:31.315 --> 00:11:33.943  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
position the Dolphin III
at the proper elevation,

212
00:11:34.026 --> 00:11:35.444  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and send the missile off.

213
00:11:35.611 --> 00:11:38.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mathematically, at least,
it should be possible

214
00:11:38.322 --> 00:11:41.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to reach the station's orbit
and in time.

215
00:11:41.242 --> 00:11:43.911  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Agreed, but in order
to reach that elevation,

216
00:11:43.994 --> 00:11:45.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
there will be
weight limitations.

217
00:11:45.955 --> 00:11:47.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm. I'd say that three

218
00:11:47.873 --> 00:11:50.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is the most we can send
out there to the station.

219
00:11:50.709 --> 00:11:51.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe] Only three, huh?

220
00:11:52.920 --> 00:11:54.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] Since I'm the only one

221
00:11:54.463 --> 00:11:56.632  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
who can move
through outer space on his own,

222
00:11:56.715 --> 00:11:58.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll go.
-[Heinrich] I'll go, too.

223
00:11:58.342 --> 00:12:01.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't know if the station
is loaded with guns.

224
00:12:01.595 --> 00:12:03.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You'll need firepower.

225
00:12:03.180 --> 00:12:05.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe] All right, then.

226
00:12:05.224 --> 00:12:08.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jet, Heinrich, me...

227
00:12:08.185 --> 00:12:09.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
we'll go.

228
00:12:09.353 --> 00:12:10.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then it's settled.

229
00:12:10.896 --> 00:12:13.691  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Let's get started
as quickly as we can.

230
00:12:13.858 --> 00:12:15.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[cyborgs] Roger.

231
00:12:24.952 --> 00:12:26.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

232
00:12:26.370 --> 00:12:27.746  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gilmore] All right.

233
00:12:27.830 --> 00:12:30.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we can believe
the public blueprints,

234
00:12:30.374 --> 00:12:32.751  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
by leaving
the station's core intact,

235
00:12:32.835 --> 00:12:36.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
uncoupling and releasing
all unnecessary modules,

236
00:12:36.297 --> 00:12:39.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we can boost the thrust
to maximum levels,

237
00:12:39.258 --> 00:12:40.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
attaining escape velocity.

238
00:12:40.718 --> 00:12:43.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Once it has left Earth's orbit,

239
00:12:43.220 --> 00:12:45.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it will then
vector around Venus,

240
00:12:45.389 --> 00:12:47.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
sufficiently changing
the trajectory

241
00:12:47.516 --> 00:12:50.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so that ultimately
it will plunge into the sun.

242
00:12:50.895 --> 00:12:52.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] Who would have guessed

243
00:12:52.188 --> 00:12:54.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
they'd make
those blueprints public?

244
00:12:54.106 --> 00:12:55.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Françoise] Technically
the listing for it

245
00:12:56.066 --> 00:12:58.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is a research station
for a private firm.

246
00:12:58.903 --> 00:13:00.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But we won't know
if it's accurate

247
00:13:00.696 --> 00:13:02.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
unless we go see firsthand.

248
00:13:02.406 --> 00:13:03.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[alarm blares]

249
00:13:03.616 --> 00:13:05.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Françoise]
The hangar hatch is open.

250
00:13:22.384 --> 00:13:23.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe] Catalina!

251
00:13:25.221 --> 00:13:27.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And where do you
think you're going?

252
00:13:29.892 --> 00:13:31.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who knows?

253
00:13:31.727 --> 00:13:34.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Weren't you supposed
to fight alongside us?

254
00:13:37.608 --> 00:13:39.944  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I mean, after all,
you were the one

255
00:13:40.027 --> 00:13:42.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
who said we had to thwart
the Emperor's scheme.

256
00:13:42.738 --> 00:13:46.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That in itself is not
a reason to fight with you.

257
00:13:46.367 --> 00:13:47.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe not, but...

258
00:13:47.993 --> 00:13:51.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
009, why are you
going into space?

259
00:13:51.580 --> 00:13:52.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

260
00:13:53.499 --> 00:13:54.917  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You may be a cyborg,

261
00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:57.795  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but outer space still
holds danger for you as well.

262
00:13:57.878 --> 00:13:59.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's no guarantee
that you'll return.

263
00:14:00.005 --> 00:14:02.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, I knew that was the case.

264
00:14:02.383 --> 00:14:04.343  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Catalina] Then how
were you able to say

265
00:14:04.426 --> 00:14:06.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that you'd do so
without hesitation?

266
00:14:06.762 --> 00:14:08.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Catalina] Keep in mind
that synthetic viruses

267
00:14:08.931 --> 00:14:11.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
have no effect on cyborgs.

268
00:14:11.267 --> 00:14:13.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Even in a world
where the entire human race

269
00:14:13.561 --> 00:14:15.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
has been subjected
to forced evolution,

270
00:14:15.938 --> 00:14:19.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
cyborgs would certainly
survive without incident.

271
00:14:19.358 --> 00:14:22.403  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So tell me, why would
you be willing to risk

272
00:14:22.486 --> 00:14:25.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
your own existence
for those miserable humans?

273
00:14:25.865 --> 00:14:28.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Joe] I can't stand by and
allow that many people to die

274
00:14:28.826 --> 00:14:32.079  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
without even knowing why,
and that's reason enough.

275
00:14:33.497 --> 00:14:36.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
On top of that,
do you have any idea

276
00:14:36.250 --> 00:14:38.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of the full extent
of your powers?

277
00:14:38.294 --> 00:14:39.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

278
00:14:39.920 --> 00:14:42.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your Accelerator
isn't merely an ability

279
00:14:42.756 --> 00:14:45.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that allows you to move around
at a high velocity.

280
00:14:45.509 --> 00:14:47.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Regardless of how much
you accelerate,

281
00:14:47.845 --> 00:14:50.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you must be able to control it.

282
00:14:50.431 --> 00:14:51.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
At those physical speeds,

283
00:14:52.057 --> 00:14:54.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
your senses should
not be able to keep pace,

284
00:14:54.768 --> 00:14:57.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but you still have
perception and control

285
00:14:57.563 --> 00:14:59.231  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and can even plan ahead.

286
00:15:00.357 --> 00:15:01.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your brain's processing speed

287
00:15:02.026 --> 00:15:05.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
has been boosted by a factor
of several hundred times.

288
00:15:05.195 --> 00:15:07.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In other words,
while you're accelerating,

289
00:15:07.990 --> 00:15:11.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
your brain is in the same state
as if it were being overclocked.

290
00:15:12.369 --> 00:15:14.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If humankind can acquire
the same powers

291
00:15:15.080 --> 00:15:18.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
through forced evolution,
The Blessed are no longer fit

292
00:15:18.375 --> 00:15:20.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to serve
as the lords of creation.

293
00:15:21.003 --> 00:15:22.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Humanity will defend itself,

294
00:15:22.755 --> 00:15:25.007  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we will all
end up perishing.

295
00:15:26.759 --> 00:15:30.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That situation
must be averted at all costs.

296
00:15:30.596 --> 00:15:33.599  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Catalina,
that undetermined element

297
00:15:33.682 --> 00:15:35.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you were mentioning earlier...

298
00:15:38.437 --> 00:15:41.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was referring to you, 009.

299
00:15:41.357 --> 00:15:42.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I...

300
00:15:42.566 --> 00:15:45.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell me, when you accelerate,

301
00:15:45.110 --> 00:15:46.904  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
what does it look like to you?

302
00:15:52.368 --> 00:15:55.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Time comes to a stop
for you in that reality.

303
00:15:55.955 --> 00:15:58.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What is it you're feeling
in those moments?

304
00:16:00.042 --> 00:16:02.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That day, I know for a fact

305
00:16:02.211 --> 00:16:03.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that you went back in time.

306
00:16:17.267 --> 00:16:19.979  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you wished,
you could even have gone back

307
00:16:20.062 --> 00:16:22.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to the time
when you were still human,

308
00:16:22.940 --> 00:16:27.403  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and yet you chose
to remain a cyborg

309
00:16:27.569 --> 00:16:29.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
who is fighting for humanity...

310
00:16:30.864 --> 00:16:32.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
without anyone knowing,

311
00:16:32.992 --> 00:16:35.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
without ever receiving thanks.

312
00:16:36.203 --> 00:16:38.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And if that's the case,
how can you go on fighting?

313
00:16:41.417 --> 00:16:44.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are times
when I do find it painful,

314
00:16:45.129 --> 00:16:46.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and I admit there are times

315
00:16:47.006 --> 00:16:49.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
when I want to escape
all this fighting,

316
00:16:49.633 --> 00:16:53.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but if it's a fight
that only I will be able to win,

317
00:16:53.595 --> 00:16:55.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I won't run away from it.

318
00:16:56.140 --> 00:17:00.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I admit I never asked
for these powers,

319
00:17:00.102 --> 00:17:03.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but if I can save
even one person by using them,

320
00:17:03.897 --> 00:17:06.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
then I'm going to accelerate
without a second thought,

321
00:17:07.484 --> 00:17:09.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
forget the past, move on.

322
00:17:10.154 --> 00:17:11.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Humph.

323
00:17:13.115 --> 00:17:17.119  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're the personification
of a good man.

324
00:17:23.834 --> 00:17:24.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Catalina!

325
00:17:50.652 --> 00:17:52.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ready on scramjet. Ignite.

326
00:17:53.155 --> 00:17:54.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Pyunma] <i>Ignited</i>.

327
00:18:26.772 --> 00:18:29.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Altitude of 50,000 meters,
maximum altitude.

328
00:18:30.067 --> 00:18:31.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Entering stratopause.

329
00:18:31.443 --> 00:18:33.070  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Prepare to fire the rocket.

330
00:18:44.540 --> 00:18:46.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Prep is done.
Starting countdown.

331
00:18:47.251 --> 00:18:50.212  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>10, 9, 8,</i>

332
00:18:50.295 --> 00:18:53.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>7, 6, 5,</i>

333
00:18:53.340 --> 00:18:55.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>4, 3,</i>

334
00:18:55.509 --> 00:18:57.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
2, 1,

335
00:18:57.636 --> 00:18:58.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>ignition.</i>

336
00:19:06.145 --> 00:19:08.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Vessel is steadily ascending.

337
00:19:11.191 --> 00:19:14.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Stand by. The booster's fuel
will be depleted soon.

338
00:19:17.072 --> 00:19:18.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

339
00:19:22.244 --> 00:19:24.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Françoise] <i>Booster separation</i>.

340
00:19:34.173 --> 00:19:36.508  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Optimal trajectory
is now achieved.

341
00:19:36.675 --> 00:19:38.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have a successful launch.

342
00:19:38.760 --> 00:19:39.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both sigh]

343
00:19:39.928 --> 00:19:41.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Gilmore] Mm.

344
00:19:41.388 --> 00:19:43.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, then I guess
I'll be heading out, too.

345
00:19:43.974 --> 00:19:46.059  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Counting on you, 007.

346
00:19:46.226 --> 00:19:48.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[G.B.] Fret not.
You can leave it to me.

347
00:19:48.478 --> 00:19:50.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If Lucy's not here
when Heinrich gets back,

348
00:19:50.814 --> 00:19:53.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it is not gonna be
a pretty sight.

349
00:19:56.320 --> 00:19:57.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Target in sight

350
00:19:57.779 --> 00:19:59.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gotcha.

351
00:19:59.323 --> 00:20:01.116  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now for the tricky part.

352
00:20:03.911 --> 00:20:05.996  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Françoise] <i>Update.</i>
<i>The unmanned supply shi</i>p

353
00:20:06.079 --> 00:20:08.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>has just docked</i>
<i>with the station.</i>

354
00:20:08.332 --> 00:20:10.042  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're on track
to change your vector.

355
00:20:10.125 --> 00:20:11.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can monitor things from here.

356
00:20:11.668 --> 00:20:12.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe] <i>Roger that</i>.

357
00:20:12.836 --> 00:20:14.713  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Françoise] <i>Are you guys ready</i>?

358
00:20:14.796 --> 00:20:15.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Joe, via brainwave]
<i>Yeah.</i>

359
00:20:16.048 --> 00:20:17.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Heinrich] <i>Anytime</i>.

360
00:20:17.132 --> 00:20:18.133  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe] <i>Just do it</i>.

361
00:20:19.426 --> 00:20:21.762  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fairing release.

362
00:20:25.265 --> 00:20:26.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] <i>Let's go</i>.

363
00:20:31.855 --> 00:20:34.024  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Françoise] <i>Remember,</i>
<i>your blood oxyge</i>n

364
00:20:34.107 --> 00:20:35.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>is only good for 15 minutes.</i>

365
00:20:35.859 --> 00:20:37.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] <i>Copy that</i>.

366
00:20:37.236 --> 00:20:38.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Heinrich]
<i>It's actually more ominous,</i>

367
00:20:38.862 --> 00:20:40.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>nothing going on.</i>

368
00:20:40.530 --> 00:20:42.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Joe] <i>It's no use</i>
<i>thinking about it</i>.

369
00:20:42.491 --> 00:20:43.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Let's keep moving in.</i>

370
00:20:49.081 --> 00:20:51.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Françoise] <i>002,</i>
<i>prepare for reverse thrust</i>.

371
00:20:51.833 --> 00:20:53.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] <i>Roger that</i>.

372
00:20:53.877 --> 00:20:55.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It's gonna be a bumpy landing.</i>

373
00:20:56.046 --> 00:20:58.465  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Heinrich] <i>I knew that</i>
<i>from the moment we teamed up</i>,

374
00:20:58.548 --> 00:21:00.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and I still came along.</i>

375
00:21:00.259 --> 00:21:01.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe] <i>Don't hold back</i>.

376
00:21:01.760 --> 00:21:06.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] <i>Okay. 3, 2, 1</i>,

377
00:21:06.098 --> 00:21:07.099  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>ignition!</i>

378
00:21:13.438 --> 00:21:14.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

379
00:21:14.773 --> 00:21:16.024  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe] <i>004</i>!

380
00:21:36.169 --> 00:21:37.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet grunts]

381
00:21:37.337 --> 00:21:38.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We came this close</i>

382
00:21:38.672 --> 00:21:40.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>to putting another man</i>
<i>in orbit.</i>

383
00:21:40.340 --> 00:21:42.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Heinrich] <i>My bad</i>.

384
00:21:42.384 --> 00:21:44.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] <i>No time for apologies</i>.

385
00:21:44.344 --> 00:21:45.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[cyborgs gasp]

386
00:21:50.058 --> 00:21:51.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Heinrich] <i>This guy again</i>?

387
00:21:51.810 --> 00:21:53.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] <i>Let's get to the airlock</i>.

388
00:22:02.529 --> 00:22:04.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hey, hurry it up.
Ten minutes O-2 left.

389
00:22:13.123 --> 00:22:14.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Joe] <i>002, come on</i>!

390
00:22:17.878 --> 00:22:19.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Wait!</i>

391
00:22:19.338 --> 00:22:21.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>002, what are you doing?</i>

392
00:22:21.965 --> 00:22:23.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>[Jet] You two go on ahead.</i>

393
00:22:23.967 --> 00:22:26.636  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm going to take care</i>
<i>of that bastard.</i>

394
00:22:34.853 --> 00:22:37.606  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>002, watch your back.</i>

395
00:22:37.689 --> 00:22:40.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Hah! Who do you think</i>
<i>you're talking to?</i>

396
00:22:40.400 --> 00:22:42.444  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I'm Jet Link, remember?!</i>

397
00:22:50.494 --> 00:22:52.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Heinrich]
<i>We need an atmospheric fill-up.</i>

398
00:22:52.954 --> 00:22:53.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Huh?</i>

399
00:22:54.081 --> 00:22:56.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Jet] <i>What's wrong? 004! 009</i>!

400
00:22:56.958 --> 00:22:58.043  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Heinrich] <i>What the hell</i>?

401
00:22:58.210 --> 00:23:00.545  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>This is not going to be good.</i>

402
00:23:00.712 --> 00:23:02.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Joe] <i>There's no atmosphere</i>
<i>in here</i>.

403
00:23:02.714 --> 00:23:04.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Not possible.
-[alarms blaring]

404
00:23:05.092 --> 00:23:08.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[gasps] In another six minutes,
you'll be out of oxygen!

405
00:23:18.021 --> 00:23:20.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[ballad playing]

406
00:23:27.739 --> 00:23:28.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
